    <title>The Kindle Paperwhite Kids is down to just $115 for October Prime Day</title>
    <content type="html">  

    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="Someone outside sitting in grass and reading on a Kindle Paperwhite Kids device" src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/XgXgbz_dyxNNPLgilvy-3XLHdQA=/0x2:997x667/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73639530/kindlepaperwhitekids.0.jpg" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Kindle Paperwhite Kids is an e-reader fit for the whole family, complete with optional parental controls.&lt;/em&gt; | Image: Amazon&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="0W8rVN"&gt;As expected, Amazon is offering some great discounts on its own devices as part of its &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/17/24244180/amazon-october-prime-day-big-deal-days-fall-dates-2024"&gt;October Prime Day event&lt;/a&gt; — including e-readers like the note-taking &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/23484927/amazon-kindle-scribe-e-reader-notetaking-pen-review"&gt;Kindle Scribe&lt;/a&gt;, which is down to $254.99 ($85 off) at &lt;a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B09BS26B8B?tag=theverge02-20" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;Amazon&lt;/a&gt;. However, the Kindle deal that really stands out is on the Kindle Paperwhite Kids. Normally $169.99, right now, it’s down to just $114.99 ($55 off) at &lt;a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0BL8S6ZPT?tag=theverge02-20" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;Amazon&lt;/a&gt;, which is $5 shy of its best price to date. &lt;/p&gt;
